name: ROCKET CITY UNITED SCARF
description:
We start our collection in the deep south with this beautiful scarf from Rocket City United. Formed in 2007, RCU have represented Huntsville and Madison, Alabama in the National Premier Soccer League since their inaugural season in 2008. The club was crowned the Southeast Division Champion the following summer. These officially licensed scarves were produced in very limited quantities, so get yours while they last and show your colors in 2011.

Designed by Stitch Invasion / Produced by Ruffneck Scarves

name: PANAMA CITY PIRATES SCARF
description:
The second scarf in our collection memorializes another club from America's deep south, the Panama City Pirates. The Pirates brought soccer to the Florida Panhandle in their debut season of 2008. The club passionately competed in the Southeast Division of the Premier Development League's Southern Conference. Unfortunately, the franchise folded after the 2009 season. This is our first scarf dedicated to those clubs that are gone but not forgotten. These scarves were produced in very limited quantities.

Designed by Stitch Invasion / Produced by Ruffneck Scarves
